  "doc_id": "42038",
  "text": "Few data on surface water contamination by medicines and hormones via land are found in literature. A selection is briefly discussed below to add further considerations to the validity of screening level surface water exposure models. Ivermectin has a sorption coefficient K om of 4500-5500 l kg −1 and is rather persistent in soil with degradation half-lives DT50 (determined at 22 °C under laboratory conditions) of 93 to 240 days (mean 187 days, n = 4) [CITATION_1] . Transport of ivermectin by drainage is to be considered negligible, since this route is not assessed in the EMEA model at Koc > 500 l kg −1",
